FBIS4-29371 "dreas117_c_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-117 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 North Korea Further on Visit by Former President Carter Further on Visit by Former President Carter `Sincere Talk' With Kim Il-song SK1706111594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1106 GMT 17 Jun 94 SK1706111594 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 17 (KCNA) -- The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song, president of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, today received Former U.S. President Jimmy Carter and his entourage on a visit to Korea. First Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs Kang Sok-chu was present on the occasion. President Kim Il-song had a sincere talk with Jimmy Carter on matters of mutual concern. He gave a luncheon for the guest.
